cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about person re-identification using deep neural networks and distance metric learning. The main focus is on computer vision and image processing, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of triplet units and distance metric learning is related to cs.MM (Multimedia), and the evaluation of the approach on challenging databases suggests relevance to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
